{"lemma":"نَوْطُ","slug":"نَوْطُ","root":"ن.#.ط","root_slug":"ن-_-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-_-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n40761"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"synonym of نَاطَ (nāṭa)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَاطَ (nāṭa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"suspended thing, what hangs"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"orden, medallion, insignia"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"small hamper hanging at a camel wherein one puts dates and the like"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40761","headword_ar":"نَوْطٌ","root":"nwT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whatever it be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is suspended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hung, from another thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) an inf. n. used as a subst.: (K:) and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that is put,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hung, upon a camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EilaAwapN","text_ar":"عِلَاوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between two halves of a load,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byn Eidolayoni","text_ar":"بين عِدْلَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or, as A 'Obeyd says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona AlEuwdayoni","text_ar":"بَيْنَ العُودَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which, if not a mistranscription, app. means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the two staves of the saddle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElAwp","text_ar":"علاوة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being thus called because it is suspended ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tunaATu","text_ar":"تُنَاطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") to the load: (Z, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"receptacle of palm-leaves, of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jul~ap","text_ar":"جُلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"containing dates"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is suspended from a camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being hung, by its handles, from the saddle of the camel of burden:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA;) such, says Az, I have heard thus called by the people of El-Bahreyn: (TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anowaATN","text_ar":"اَنْوَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S. K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyaATN","text_ar":"نِيَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, K;) the former is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawoTN","text_ar":"نَوْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the general sense first mentioned above: and also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is suspended"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuw~iTa","text_ar":"نُوِّطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in two copies of the S, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwTa","text_ar":"نُوطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the camel when he is loaded:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAliyqu","text_ar":"مَعَالِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"things suspended to a beast of burden; such as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qumoqumap","text_ar":"قُمْقُمَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qirobap","text_ar":"قِرْبَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miToharap","text_ar":"مِطْهَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) It is said in a proverb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaATK bagayori A^anowaATK","text_ar":"عَاطٍ بَغَيْرِ اَنْوَاطٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Taking"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reaching to take"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without"},{"kind":"text","text":"there being there"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything suspended;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is like the saying “ Driving by singing without having a camel ” (S, L, See also art"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ETw","text_ar":"عطو"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And in another proverb."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino A^aEoyaA","text_ar":"اـِنْ اَعْيَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaEiyru fazidohu nawoTFA","text_ar":"البَعِيرُ فَزِدْهُ نَوْطًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If the camel be fatigued, add thou to him an appendage to his full load"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning, if he be slow and inobsequious in his pace, do not thou lighten his burden: (K:) accord. to As,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino A^aEoyaA fazidohu nawoTFA","text_ar":"اـِنْ اَعْيَا فَزِدْهُ نَوْطًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a proverb relating to the pressing a niggardly man. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu A^anowaATK","text_ar":"ذَاتُ اَنْوَاطٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A particular tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of great size,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which was worshipped in the time of ignorance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"said by IAth to be the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a particular gum-acacia-free"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samurap","text_ar":"سَمُرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to which the believers in a plurality of gods used to suspend their weapons, and around which they used to circuit."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~awoTu Almu*abo*ibu","text_ar":"النَّوْطُ المُذَبْذِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in a trad. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The leg of a rider,"},{"kind":"text","text":"from fatigue or some other cause, ever"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dangling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moving to and fro."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Z","Az"]}]}}